cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper is about optimizing query evaluations in web search, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) in computer science. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. Reinforcement learning (RL) is used to improve the candidate generation step, which involves selecting a small set of documents from a large collection of web pages. RL is a subfield of machine learning (ML), which includes sub-categories such as cs.LG (machine learning), cs.CL (computation and language), and cs.AI (artificial intelligence). Finally, the paper also involves reducing the number of index blocks accessed, which is related to data structures and algorithms, falling under the sub-category cs.DS (data structures and algorithms).
